#### Elections in the 1770s

At the 1776 general election, [Arthur Hill, Viscount Kilwarlin](/Arthur_Hill,_2nd_Marquess_of_Downshire) and [Robert Stewart](/Robert_Stewart,_1st_Marquess_of_Londonderry) were elected unopposed. [^7]

At the by-election in 1771, following Ward's creation as Baron Bangor... a predictable sequence.

#### Elections in the 1760s

At the 1768 general election, Roger Hall and [Bernard Ward](/Bernard_Ward,_1st_Viscount_Bangor) were elected unopposed. [^7] More unopposed returns. Remarkable.

